{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"**Topology Summary**\n\nSingle-stage MOS common-source amplifier with an NMOS pull-down gain device and a diode-connected PMOS active load. Use exact port nodes `Vin` and `Vout`. The output node `Vout` is the shared NMOS drain and PMOS gate/drain node.\n\n**Device/Function List**\n\n- `VDD` source: independent DC supply from `VDD` to `0`, value `5 V`.\n- `Vin` source: independent voltage source from `Vin` to `0`, with DC bias around `1.5 V` and AC magnitude `1`.\n- `M1` NMOS common-source transistor:\n  - drain = `Vout`\n  - gate = `Vin`\n  - source = `0`\n  - bulk = `0`\n  - function: input-controlled pull-down/gain device.\n- `M2` PMOS diode-connected active load:\n  - drain = `Vout`\n  - gate = `Vout`\n  - source = `VDD`\n  - bulk = `VDD`\n  - function: nonlinear load/current source-like pull-up with local diode feedback.\n- Optional load resistor from `Vout` to `0` only if needed, preferably omitted unless required; if used, choose `50k` within the allowed `10k` to `100k`.\n\n**Bias/Reference Strategy**\n\nGround is node `0`. `VDD` is fixed at `5 V`. `Vin` must have an explicit DC gate bias, preferably `1.5 V`, so `M1` conducts with `VGS > Vth`. The expected DC operating point should settle with `0 < Vout < 5 V`, both MOSFETs on, and `M1` preferably in saturation with:\n\n```spice\nVDS >= VGS - Vth\n```\n\nFor `M1`, this means `Vout >= Vin - 0.7 V`.\n\n**Signal Or Feedback Path**\n\nSmall-signal input at `Vin` modulates NMOS drain current. Increased `Vin` increases `M1` current, pulling `Vout` lower, so voltage gain should be inverting.\n\nThe PMOS gate-drain short at `Vout` creates local negative feedback in the load: as `Vout` moves, PMOS overdrive changes, producing a finite small-signal diode resistance from `Vout` to `VDD`. This load reduces gain compared with an ideal current-source load but stabilizes the DC operating point.\n\n**SPICE/Netlist Constraints**\n\n- Final filename must be `p15.cir`.\n- Preserve exact node names `Vin` and `Vout`.\n- Include `.op`.\n- Include `.ac dec 20 1 1e9`.\n- Do not use subcircuits.\n- Do not use placeholder model names.\n- Include explicit `.model` statements for NMOS and PMOS with:\n  - NMOS: `VTO=0.7`, `KP=100u`\n  - PMOS: `VTO=-0.7`, `KP=50u`\n- Use `W=50u L=1u` for `M1`.\n- Use `W=100u L=1u` for `M2`.\n\n**Failure Risks To Avoid**\n\n- Do not leave `Vin` floating or define it as AC-only without DC bias.\n- Do not swap PMOS source/drain such that the source is not at `VDD`.\n- Do not forget the PMOS diode connection: both gate and drain must be tied to `Vout`.\n- Do not tie NMOS bulk anywhere except `0`.\n- Do not tie PMOS bulk anywhere except `VDD`.\n- Avoid choosing too low a `Vin` DC bias; below about `1.2 V`, `M1` may be weak or off.\n- Avoid adding a strong resistive load that dominates the PMOS diode load and destroys the requested topology behavior."}}
